  "prompt": "How widely accepted are credit cards at small businesses and restaurants in Barbados?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, credit cards are generally accepted at many businesses and restaurants in Barbados, but acceptance can vary widely, especially among small businesses. Larger hotels, restaurants, and tourist-oriented shops typically accept major credit cards like Visa and MasterCard. However, some smaller establishments, local restaurants, and markets may only accept cash. \n\nIt's always a good idea for travelers to have some cash on hand for places that do not accept cards, especially in more rural areas or at local markets. Additionally, it's wise to check in advance or inquire directly with specific businesses to confirm their payment methods.",
